Package org.neo4j.internal.id.indexed

Class IndexedIdGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.id.indexed.IndexedIdGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, IdGenerator, IdSequence, ConsistencyCheckable
    public class IndexedIdGenerator
extends Object
implements IdGenerator
    At the heart of this free-list sits a GBPTree, containing all deleted and freed ids. The tree is used as a bit-set and since it's sorted then it can be later extended to allocate multiple consecutive ids. Another design feature of this free-list is that it's crash-safe, that is if the marker(PageCursorTracer) is only used for applying committed data.

      • STRICTLY_PRIORITIZE_FREELIST_DEFAULT

        private static final boolean STRICTLY_PRIORITIZE_FREELIST_DEFAULT
        Default value whether or not to strictly prioritize ids from freelist, as opposed to allocating from high id. Given a scenario where there are multiple concurrent calls to nextId(PageCursorTracer) or nextIdBatch(int, boolean, PageCursorTracer) and there are free ids on the freelist, some perhaps cached, some not. Thread noticing that there are no free ids cached will try to acquire scanner lock and if it succeeds it will perform a scan and place found free ids in the cache and return. Otherwise:
        • If false: thread will allocate from high id and return, to not block id allocation request.
        • If true: thread will await lock released and check cache afterwards. If no id is cached even then it will allocate from high id.
        See Also:

      • LARGE_CACHE_CAPACITY

        Constant Field Values

      • STARTING_GENERATION

        private static final long STARTING_GENERATION
        First generation the tree entries will start at. Generation will be incremented each time an IndexedIdGenerator is opened, i.e. not for every checkpoint. Generation is used to do lazy normalization of id states, so that DELETED ids from a previous generation looks like FREE in the current session. Updates to tree items (except for recovery) will reset the generation that of the current session.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • atLeastOneIdOnFreelist

        private final AtomicBoolean atLeastOneIdOnFreelist
        Means of communicating whether or not there are stored free ids that FreeIdScanner could pick up. Is also cleared by FreeIdScanner as soon as it notices that it has run out of stored free ids.

      • generation

        private final long generation
        Current generation of this id generator. Generation is used to normalize id states so that a deleted id of a previous generation can be seen as free in the current generation. Generation is bumped on restart.

      • needsRebuild

        private final boolean needsRebuild
        Internal state kept between constructor and start(FreeIds, PageCursorTracer), whether or not to rebuild the id generator from the supplied FreeIds.

      • highestWrittenId

        private final AtomicLong highestWrittenId
        Highest ever written id in this id generator. This is used to not lose track of ids allocated off of high id that are not committed. See more in IdRangeMarker.

        private volatile boolean started
        false after construction and before a call to IdGenerator.start(FreeIds, PageCursorTracer), where false means that operations made this freelist is to be treated as recovery operations. After a call to IdGenerator.start(FreeIds, PageCursorTracer) the operations are to be treated as normal operations.

      • markHighestWrittenAtHighId

        public void markHighestWrittenAtHighId()
        A peculiar being this one. It's for the import case where all records are written w/o even touching the id generator. When all have been written the id generator is told that it should consider highest written where it's at right now So that it won't mark all ids as deleted on the first write (the id bridging).
